items.title: Colorizer
items.body:
For supporting the application of lookup tables other than those provided in datasets, a new ReaderWrapper `Colorizer` has been added which takes an implementation of the new interface `LutSource` to convert one `byte[]` to another.

**NOT READY FOR TESTING; API REVIEW ONLY**

Testing:
 * `./bfconvert -colorize fire INPUT OUTPUT` should produce results similar to applying a LUT in ImageJ

items.title: Colorizer
items.body:
If a pixels object has a param of the form `{"lut": "fire"}`,
then an `ImageJLutSource` will be applied in the reader wrapper
stack. This will make it possible for the clients to manipulate the
bytes which are returned from Bio-Formats before, e.g., rendering
takes place.

**NOT READY FOR TESTING; API REVIEW ONLY**

Until the `params` values from the database are exposed to the clients, it will be difficult to test this from the UI. /cc @jburel @mtbc 

--depends-on openmicroscopy/bioformats#1551

items.title: Color
items.body:
Enhancements to color handling.
Improved algorithm for hex to rgb conversion.
All colors, including x11 colors are parsed to a Color object and converted to rgb/rgba internally. This is needed in order to make expandShorthands and createShorthand methods work with named (x11) colors.
New methods for color conversion to/from hsl and rgb.
